REGISTRY AUTHORITATIVE (P5.1): Registry manifest + `.j2` templates
are canonical. SKILL.md derived. If conflict, registry wins.
PUBLIC VISIBILITY: `visibility: public` — no hidden audit controls.
NO FABRICATION: Metric computed from evidence counts only. Blockers
derived from actual `findings`, `gate_results`,
`proposed_regressions`. No synthetic config references. No synthetic
regression counts.
CONVERGENCE INDEPENDENT: Separate `.j2` template; does not duplicate
`report` phase logic. Uses current supplied findings and phase-tagged
gate results. `previous_metric` is optional comparable evidence; when
absent, improvement_pct is null and threshold convergence still applies.
CNS SPAN EMITTED: `cns.lora.convergence` is registered, so the span
is always emitted. Output states `cns_span_emitted: true`.
MINIMAL ARTIFACT: This template produces exactly the metric, verdict,
and blockers — no extra synthesis (that is `report.j2`
responsibility).
